flavourText: <size:26>{"Such dedication for so many years,
all for a couple extra letters at the front of your name..."}
The acolytes congratulated the lucky groom for becoming one with the goddess.
<size:28>{Scaly beast of the skies,
watching with his golden eyes.
Shadow that blocks out the sun,
it's too late for you to run.}

<size:25>{"To know for what you fight. To get up again when you've been struck down. To outmanoeuvre someone faster, trick someone smarter, crush someone stronger. That's what it takes to claim the crown."
- Daresso, the King of Swords}
By the time their eyes meet,
the dark deal has long since been made,
and his fate long since sealed.
Wealth can, in fact, buy happiness.
Even the most beautiful of transformations can still have a dark side.
<size:30>{In a land far away lived
a maiden most fair.
Her smile melted the coldest
of hearts, her song made
men and beast cry,
her beauty unparalleled;
Divine.}
Know thine enemy better than you know thyself.
There are countless people, countless stories, and countless eras, but there is one place that, for a time, each of us loved and was loved. It matters. We matter.
<size:27>{Fire filled the sky that night
Chaos reigned
Where the shards fell
All was destroyed
-Jozen Kasigi, retelling an urban legend of the Cataclysm}
A good spy doesn't forget she's gone undercover.
<size:30>{He wandered the bone-filled depths hoping each corner would be his last.
Eventually, he found Light.}
We tried to tell him to get his head checked.
<size:28>{I never truly understood the depths of my insanity,
until I realized the voices beckoning me towards the abyss,
were none other than my own.}
<size:28>{No man sees all, but you'll see more than some see in a lifetime.}
Life isn't what you make of it, it's already been made for you.
<size:25>{"Glimmers of benevolence,
Shrouded a lacquered lust for power,
Yet still they followed his influence."}
<size:30>{A King Loved By All,
A Shadow Awaiting Nightfall,
A Speaker Howling Away,
A Hunter Seeking Prey}
<size:27>{The mighty warriors traded in blows, the nimble archers in arrows, yet it was the brazen thaumaturgists who would bring catastrophe to all.}
Genius knows no limits.
Even in darkness you may find a friend.
Good and Evil can be woven together to become something greater than either.
When you find what you're looking for, it's never quite right. When you have what you desire, yet you still want more.
"Many believe murder is a grisly, grim, and grotesque crime. Then there are those who simply make art of it."
"They said I needed my head examined, but I'd rather just take yours." - Klopek the Cannibal
"How many lives have you consumed?"
"How many times have you blinked?"
<size:27>{A wanderer in the wild strives
Against countless foes he survives
A fool pursues a quest contrived
By the gift of the witch, alive.}
If the path to divinity were simple, we'd all be gods.
<size:25>{Seeking shelter from the night,
in the warmth of the run-down inn,
erstwhile foes put aside the fight,
to bond over whiskey and gin.}
I have a headache, can anyone find me a nurse?
Time dismantles all things eventually, but some wish to accelerate the process.
"I don't believe in karma. If it were real, I would never win."
Scarier than any criminal is an innocent man in chains, for when he breaks free, his revenge will be justified.
<size:31>{As their civilisation crumbled, the Vaal looked to their queen. In her, they saw a way out. In them, she saw a burden she was happy to free herself from.}
Their whims left unknown,
Their life left for others.
His brother would not atone, so he took his brother's life, and with it, his sins.
The harvest ended, the floods began.
"It was as though my very thoughts were breaking... fracturing into tiny motes to be lost on the wind."
Let these fine arrows pack a punch.
In the hands of a master craftsman, a worthless pebble can adorn the crown of a king.
You cannot journey to new lands until you have the courage to leave the safety of home.
Her innocence and grace were enough to tame even the wildest of beasts.
Luck is a fool's game, and I know plenty of rich fools.
<size:31>{Brutus' first innovation as Lord Incarcerator was a weighted chain around every neck so that his prisoners would forever bow to him.}
If you beckon the
Lord of Lightning,
do not be surprised
when you are struck.
Never dying, yet not living,
Endlessly they wander
beneath the harvest moon.
<size:31>{There is no mistake so great that it cannot be undone.}
<size:26>{The fortunate find
generosity in the divine.}
The threads of fate are the strongest ties.
<size:26>{Many were slain by the sword king
Their blood decorating his ring
Those who retreated were slaughtered
Those who fought bravely were honoured}
<size:31>{The Eternals lauded his valour. The Karui relished his defeat. Yet the final thoughts of Marceus Lioneye were naught but lament for his pride.}
If you wish to rush into strange places, be prepared to face strange things.
No man may hope to turn back the storm. You can only hope you do not attract its ire.
Jump right in,
But beware
Of things broken
Or beyond compare.
When you dwell in total darkness, even the faintest light may guide you out.
Though the years weakened his mind, his body remained deadly as ever.
The fight is the easy part. It's the years of training that'll kill you.
If enough people believe something to be true, whether or not it is becomes irrelevant.
If you look hard enough for hidden meaning, you will find it.
<size:29>{"I swore to use my position to help the people. What good is power when it just accumulates on the already-powerful?" - Erasmus, Imperial Gemcutter}
It is a mortal man's folly to seek power beyond his comprehension.
"No man can best me, no demon can fell me. For I vanquish all with my axe!"
I've never come upon a ship I could not command. I have however met sailors that were not willing to be led.
"More! I want more!" - Faendris, the Insatiable
A tower built of the strongest stone is not eternal; a towering intellect is not enlightened.
It's sad times we live in when a friendship has a price people are willing to pay.
<size:31>{A month's work, a year's wages, a foolish shortcut through a Rhoa's nest, and a grieving bride-to-be, who never received her betrothed's great gift.}
Wrapped in the glory of the heavens, she comes to mete out justice for the fallen.
"Hold your tongue before I claim it." - Doedre Darktongue
A map is only useful if you know where you stand.
"The house always wins... except when I do."
When there is no other choice, even the meekest whisper can bring about the greatest storm.
"Some see our mortal flesh as a limitation. I see it as an opportunity for vast, miraculous improvements."
- Shavronne of Umbra
The Atlas is our prison, and our only defence. She is our only hope, and our certain doom.
When the world burned, the greedy burned with it, while the clever left as paupers.
Even the most learned man is a fool to his own fate.
<size:26>{They came from far and wide under a common banner.
They sought companionship and competition,
but found a treasure none had foreseen.}
<size:23>{Vintage or crafted, Glittering and shiny
Dusty or glittering, huge or tiny
Secured within a chest
or unearthed from your mining
Find jewellery everywhere,
no need for divining!
So why is it so hard
to figure out which one to wear?
This one makes me stronger,
but does it match my hair?}
True to his title,
Voll, newly crowned,
had many of the
Eternal Empire's signature
extravagances destroyed.
<size:30>{A weapon, a shelter, a prison.
The web's purpose changes
with the spider's needs.
A lesson we should
take to heart.}
<size:26>{Hemmingsworth 6:10 - "And the fox gazed out from the brambles, unreachable and smirking."}
"There is no right or wrong choice, no best or worst. There are only choices and their consequences."
Sometimes your greatest enemy is the only one keeping you breathing.
All that is flawed is worthless. The slightest error, and this might as well be trash.
You'll never know the things you miss if you keep your eyes closed
Warriors of a distant land, you embark on a journey from which you may not return, but which we will be all the better for.
A lucky number
For us all
To help us through
The perils told.
For every threat you spy in the shadows, there are two others you don't.
Embrace horror.
Bathe in its beauty.
<size:28>{They gave the stone life. Over eons spent bathed in Corruption, that life evolved.}
Be like water, friend.
The house always wins.
"Sometimes, the most beautiful treasures...are the ones you cannot have."
- Beryl, Survivor from the Azurite Mines
A taste of power brings a hunger for more.
Primed, curved and sleek.
Decisive and final.
For malice and righteousness.
There's but one solution.
Lioneye looked to the heights of glorious victory. And thus he missed the defeat right under his nose.
Greed is a hunger that only grows as you feed it
A life lost, A legacy born.

flavourText: Without the ability to weep, the heart hardens against both the pure and the corrupt.
Accumulating wealth has its own costs.
Nothing can be heard above the din or seen amongst the turmoil. The senses are shattered. All is left to fate.
Necromancers, believe me, are more terrifying than their thralls.
<size:34>{He dispels dark realms
until mortal sufferings
yield to hopeful light.}
Fall into endless night; a voyage into an ocean of oblivion.
Those whose hands are their livelihood know the importance of keeping them safe and warm.
Method transcends shape and size. Do something in parallel long enough, and you will always find
another way.
<size:31>{"Daughter of catastrophe, mother of pain. Amongst the filth of Wraeclast, she wanders, and her wrath follows." - Quintoon the Returned}
"This one? It is NOT for sale. You would sooner pry it from my lifeless hand."
- Jonf Darontos, Ringmaker
The first to travel are often rewarded for their journey, but all the treasure in the world cannot bring back those that are lost.
<size:30>{Taste not of their
forbidden fruit.
Theirs is a harvest of
the darkest kind,
twisted, rotten and
damned for eternity.}
Trying to bring your vision to life is enough to drive you mad.
<size:29>{A mind as quick as lightning,
fists as hard as stone,
a heart that burns with fury,
and eyes that chill to the bone.}
Turn the crank,
close your eyes,
and pray to the gods
for a pleasant surprise.
